content:
Other Changes in Product Catalog Management

To include or exclude picklist values from product classification attributes, product attribute definitions, or overridden product attributes, you can now use the Include or Exclude Picklist Values action next to the attributes.

Previously, you used the Excluded Picklist Values field when you edited the product classification attribute, product attribute definition, or overridden product attribute. The Excluded Picklist Values field is no longer available.

Additionally, to validate the component count, and to ensure that every product attribute in a static and simple bundle has a default value, and that the group cardinality is in compliance, you can now use Validate Product Definition. Previously, this functionality was called Validate Product Bundle.

When a group has multiple products, click Show More to see 10 products at a time. Previously, Show More expanded to show five products.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How:

To include or exclude picklist values from product classification attributes of the picklist data type, click Include or Exclude Picklist Values.

To include or exclude picklist values from product attribute definitions of the picklist data type, click Include or Exclude Picklist Values next to the overridden inherited attribute.

To include or exclude picklist values from overridden product attributes of the picklist data type, click Include or Exclude Picklist Values next to the overridden product attribute.

To validate the product definition, click Validate Product Definition.
title: Product Catalog Management Updates
